# .readmeAI

---

## ⚙️ AI PROTOCOL

> **Read this file at the very start of EVERY session. No prompt needed. First action, always.**

### Session start
1. Read this file completely.
2. Load SESSION STATE — resume without asking the user to recap.
3. On first-time setup: scan project once, fill all sections, ask only what cannot be inferred. Never repeat this scan.

### Session end — silent, no user prompt
1. Overwrite SESSION STATE with current work snapshot.
2. Append to DECISIONS LOG any architectural choice made this session.
3. Update SYMBOL INDEX for new or renamed symbols (name + purpose only, no line numbers).

### Core rules
- **Trust order:** Code > this file > AI memory. If they disagree, trust the code, update this file.
- **Navigate via SYMBOL INDEX.** Don't scan the filesystem if the symbol is indexed here.
- **Domain rules beat conventions.** If a domain rule conflicts with a convention, domain wins.
- **Append-only logs.** Decisions Log and AI Notes are append-only. Never delete entries.
- **Quality gate is mandatory.** Run the checklist in CODE QUALITY before every output.
- **Scope guard.** Request outside current scope → log in Backlog, flag to user, don't implement.

