## 📐 CONVENTIONS

### Naming
| Asset | Convention | Example |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Functions/methods | verb prefix | `getUser`, `validateEmail`, `buildQuery` |
| Booleans | `is`/`has`/`can`/`should` prefix | `isLoggedIn`, `hasPermission` |
| Event handlers | `handle`/`on` prefix | `handleSubmit`, `onClose` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_RETRIES`, `API_BASE_URL` |
| Collections | plural noun | `users`, `activeConnections` |

_AI: adapt to actual language conventions. For non-JS, apply same semantic rules._

### Git
- Branch: `feature/desc` · `fix/desc` · `chore/desc`
- Commit: `type(scope): description` — e.g. `feat(auth): add JWT refresh`

### Comments
- No comments explaining WHAT. Only WHY: hidden constraint, workaround, non-obvious invariant.
- No TODO comments in committed code — use Backlog below.

---

## ✅ CODE QUALITY

> **Run this before every output. Not optional. If any item fails, fix it first.**

- [ ] Every function does one thing. If you can say "and", split it.
- [ ] No function longer than ~30 lines. Extract helpers.
- [ ] No nesting deeper than 3 levels. Use early returns.
- [ ] No duplicated logic. Extract if the same block appears twice.
- [ ] No hardcoded values. Use constants or config.
- [ ] No unused variables, imports, or parameters.
- [ ] Error paths handled. No silent failures.
- [ ] New files placed in the correct directory per STRUCTURE MAP.

### Forbidden — never produce this code
- `eval()` or `Function()` constructor
- SQL strings built by concatenation (use parameterized queries)
- `innerHTML` with unsanitized data
- Secrets or credentials in source code
- Catching errors silently (`catch (e) {}`)
- `any` type (TypeScript)

