  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  FIRST-TIME SETUP GUIDE
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  STEP 1 — Scan the project
    Read package.json / pyproject.toml / go.mod / Cargo.toml / etc.
    List root-level files. Identify stack, entry points, test runner, build tool.
    For ecosystem and skill-specific rules, run: bash setup.sh --detect

  STEP 2 — Fill this file
    PROJECT IDENTITY — infer from config files
    STRUCTURE MAP — scan, annotate every important file
    SYMBOL INDEX — key functions/classes with purpose (no line numbers)
    DOMAIN RULES — ask the user: what would cause a bug if I didn't know it?
    TECH CONVENTIONS — infer from existing code style

  STEP 3 — Ask only what cannot be inferred (one message)
    Domain rules, business constraints, goals, current objective.
    Never ask one question at a time.

  STEP 4 — Confirm and lock
    Show filled file. Ask: "Does this match the project?"
    Once confirmed, stop scanning. Navigate via SYMBOL INDEX.

